              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Location-specific service pages targeting "[service] in [city]" queries, and blog posts answering locally relevant questions like "cost of dental implants in Denver" or "best time to replace HVAC in Phoenix." Informational local content fills niches the local pack doesn't serve.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">How do local organic results differ from the local pack?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>The local pack (Google Map with 3 listings) ranks based on your Google Business Profile, proximity, and review signals. Local organic results rank based on your website content, backlinks, and local relevance factors. You can appear in one without the other, and appearing in both maximises page coverage.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">How long does it take to rank in local organic results?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>For a new page targeting a local keyword with moderate competition, expect 60-90 days to see initial rankings and 3-6 months for stable top-5 positions. More competitive markets or thin content may take longer. Strong internal linking and local backlinks accelerate the timeline.</p></div></div>
